<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Starting With EX-</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Scrabble Words Finder · English Solver · Word of the Day</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The EX- prefix means "out of" or "former" and carries a natural scoring advantage thanks to the X tile's 8-point value. Every EX- word starts with at least 9 points before you even count the rest of the letters. With 400+ valid words, this prefix turns ordinary racks into scoring opportunities.</p>

<p>Because X is one of only two tiles worth 8 points, knowing your EX- words lets you deploy it effectively rather than getting stuck with it late-game.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why EX- Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
